'''Atlantic City Fashion Week''' or '''ACFW''' is a [[fashion event]] held two times every year, Spring and Fall.

The event features activities that include fashion shows, seminars, celebrity appearances, retail events, networking opportunities and industry parties.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|title=New custom bespoke suit model from LeGrand Leseur|url=http://made-to-measure-suits.bgfashion.net/article/10426/44/New-custom-bespoke-suit-model-from-LeGrand-Leseur}}</ref> Atlantic City Fashion Week features an eclectic group of designers, national retailers, boutiques and novice design students. Designers from [[England]], [[Hungary]], [[Russia]], [[Australia]], [[Haiti]], [[Trinidad]], Senegal, the Dominican Republic and all parts of the United States have showcased their collections at our runway event. Retailers have included [[Michael Kors]], [[Tommy Bahama]], [[OshKosh B'Gosh]], Invicta, [[Brooks Brothers]], Tiffany's and [[Abercrombie and Fitch]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mark Your Calendar: Atlantic City Fashion Week Is Coming|url=http://njmonthly.com/articles/style-shopping/susan-on-style/atlantic-city-fashion-week-february-26-28/|publisher=[[New Jersey Monthly]]}}</ref> Atlantic City Fashion Week has also been a showcase for designers from the hit television series [[Project Runway]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Hamilton Mall hosts prom 'Catwalk Jam'|url=http://www.pressofatlanticcity.com/life/hamilton-mall-hosts-prom-catwalk-jam/article_6b6daf29-b301-541c-b5b0-008d6d77027d.html|publisher=[[The Press of Atlantic City]]}}</ref> Those designers have included Dom Streater, Helen Castillo and Lantie Foster, as well as Philadelphia's men's designer LeGrand Leseur.<ref name="auto"/><ref name="auto1">{{cite web|title=Atlantic City Fashion Week: LeGrand Leseur men's coats collection|url=http://made-to-measure-suits.bgfashion.net/article/10794/56/Atlantic-City-Fashion-Week-LeGrand-Leseur-mens-coats-collection|publisher=Be Global Fashion Network}}</ref> Atlantic City Fashion Week has held its events at a variety of venues on the world-famous Atlantic City Boardwalk including "The Pier Shops at Caesars" (now "[[Playground Pier]]"), [[Bally's Atlantic City]], and the [[The Claridge Hotel (Atlantic City)|Claridge Hotel]].<ref name="auto1"/>

==History==
{{expand section|date=May 2015}}
Atlantic City Fashion Week was Founded in 2011, by Lamont and Jeana Bowling, the founders of fashionSTYLE Magazine and KingBee Media LLC.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hamilton Mall to host prom fashion show|url=http://www.shorenewstoday.com/events/hamilton-mall-to-host-prom-fashion-show/article_4730a600-da26-11e4-8c83-f7e28ec775b8.html|publisher=Shore News Today}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Atlantic City Fashion Week brings red carpet swag to the beach city|url=http://www.courierpostonline.com/story/entertainment/2015/02/27/atlantic-city-fashion-week-brings-red-carpet-swag-beach-city/24105357/|publisher=[[Courier-Post]]}}</ref>

