{{Infobox recurring event |image = Dorset 100 5690.JPG |imagesize = |caption = [[Dorset (sheep)|Dorset]] ram at the 2010 festival |begins = First full weekend in May |ends = Sunday |date = |frequency = Annual |location = [[West Friendship, Maryland]] |first = 1973 |last = |participants = Knitters, sheep breeders, wool spinners |footnotes = }}
The '''Maryland Sheep and Wool Festival''' is the largest and longest-running showcase of [[domestic sheep]] and [[wool]] in the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=A Mild and Woolly Adventure; 'Hobbyist' Farmers Tend Flocks In Effort to Reconnect With Land |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-415179.html |quote=In Maryland, some enterprising farmers have turned the Maryland Sheep and Wool Festival into what organizers say is the largest and longest-running event of ... |work=[[Washington Post]] |date=March 24, 2001 |accessdate=2009-02-09 }}</ref> The 2010 festival was the 37th consecutive. It is held at the [[Howard County Fairgrounds]] in [[West Friendship, Maryland]].
==History== The festival was started in 1973.<ref name=fest>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Md. sheep and wool fest phenomenal in 30th year |url=http://www.americanfarm.com/TopStory7-01-03sheep.html |quote=It’s hard to believe it’s been 30 years for the Maryland Sheep and Wool Festival. These sentiments were echoed time and again during the festival’s run May 3 and 4, 2003, at the Howard County Fairgrounds in West Friendship, Md. The festival has grown from a small show of wool sheep held in Carroll County 30 years ago, to a national phenomenon attracting 70,000 people from all over the world. |work=American Farm |date=2003 |accessdate=2009-02-09 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060319024443/http://www.americanfarm.com/TopStory7-01-03sheep.html |archivedate = 2006-03-19}}</ref> In 2003 it attracted over 70,000 people.<ref name=fest/> The 2014 festival was the 40th consecutive. It is sponsored by the Maryland Sheep Breeders Association. The festival's purpose is to "educate the public about sheep and wool". It is organized and staffed by volunteers from both the sheep breeding and fiber communities.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sheepandwool.org/index.html |title=Maryland Sheep and Wool Festival |accessdate=2009-02-09 |quote= |publisher=Maryland Sheep and Wool Festival }}</ref>
It is held annually during the first weekend in May at the [[Howard County, Maryland|Howard County]] Fairgrounds in [[West Friendship, Maryland]].<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Curtain falls on 31st annual edition of Maryland Sheep and Wool Festival |url=http://www.americanfarm.com/TopStory5-11-04e.html |quote=The Maryland Sheep and Wool Festival, held the first full weekend in May each year at the Howard County Fairgrounds in West Friendship, Md., celebrated its 31st anniversary May 1–2, and attendance proved the event is as popular as ever. |work=American Farm |date=2004 |accessdate=2009-02-09 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070629141852/http://www.americanfarm.com/TopStory5-11-04e.html |archivedate = 2007-06-29}}</ref> It has vendors of [[wool]] yarn, and judging of more than 30 [[sheep]] breeds. Vendors of other fiber-producing livestock such as [[Cashmere wool|goats]], [[angora rabbit]]s, [[llama]]s, and [[alpaca]] also attend.
The festival includes live music, a parade of breeds, a [[sheep to shawl contest]], and [[border collie]] demonstrations.<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Maryland Sheep and Wool Festival |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/gog/misc-events/maryland-sheep-and-wool-festival,1041637.html |quote=The festival also includes live music, a long line of fairground concessions, sheep to pet, border collie demonstrations and vendors selling more kinds of wool and sheep knicknacks than you can count. |work=[[Washington Post]] |date=2006 |accessdate=2009-02-09 }}</ref> Food vendors sell various lamb dishes including lamb burgers, [[gyros]], and lamb sausage. There are also lamb cooking contests and lamb cooking demonstrations.
