The '''Sings Like Hell''' music series is a popular monthly concert series based at the historic [[Lobero Theater]] in [[Santa Barbara, California]].<ref name="SLH">{{cite journal |last=Dicks |first=Brett Leigh |title=''Ten Years of Hell'' |newspaper=[[Santa Barbara Independent]] |issue= |date=September 28, 2006 |url=http://www.independent.com/news/2006/sep/14/ten-years-of-hell/ |page= |deadurl=yes |accessdate=November 28, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161129210047/http://www.independent.com/news/2006/sep/14/ten-years-of-hell/ |archivedate=November 29, 2016 |df= }}</ref>
==Series background == Created by Austin-based music producer, Peggie Jones, Sings Like Hell was first held in August, 1997, and has since featured almost 240 shows staged across a twenty-year period. Drawing its name from the 1993 [[Peter Case]] album, [[Sings Like Hell]], the subscriber-based series features two, six-show programs each year, primarily highlighting the talent of singers-songwriters using a variety of styles and influences, from [[Americana (music)|Americana]] to [[Blues]], [[Folk music|Folk]], [[Folk music|Roots music]] and [[World Music]].<ref name="SLH"/> Featured artists have included among others, [[Jeff Bridges]] and the Abiders,<ref name="JB">{{cite journal |last=Comingore |first=Ali |title=''Jeff Bridges at Sings Like Hell'' |newspaper=[[Santa Barbara Independent]] |issue= |date=March 9, 2011 |url=http://www.independent.com/news/2011/mar/09/jeff-bridges-sings-hell/ |page= |deadurl=yes |accessdate=November 28, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161129210049/http://www.independent.com/news/2011/mar/09/jeff-bridges-sings-hell/ |archivedate=November 29, 2016 |df= }}</ref> [[Jackson Browne]],<ref name="JB2">{{cite journal|last=Dicks|first=Brett Leigh |title=''A New Home for Hell - Sings Like Hell launches next series in a new venue'' |newspaper=[[Santa Barbara News-Press]] |issue= |date=June 28, 2013 |url=http://www.newspress.com/Top/Article/article.jsp?Section=SCENE&ID=566730397325590589&Archive=true/ |page= |accessdate=November 28, 2016 }}</ref> [[Emmylou Harris]], [[Jason Isbell]], [[Bonnie Riatt]], [[Damien Rice]], [[Richard Thompson (musician)|Richard Thompson]], and [[Gillian Welch]].
==External links== *[http://www.singslikehell.org/ Sings Like Hell website]
