{{Infobox music festival | music_festival_name = The Summer Slaughter Tour | caption = The Most Extreme Tour of the Year | location = * United States (2007–present) * Mexico (2010) * Canada (2008, 2009, 2014) * Europe (2008) * Australia/New Zealand (2009) | years_active = 2007–present | founders = Ash Avildsen | genre = [[Death metal]], [[metalcore]], [[progressive metal]], [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] | website = {{url|http://www.sumerianrecords.com/summerslaughter}} }} '''The Summer Slaughter Tour''' is an annual [[heavy metal music]] tour held every year since 2007. It originated in North America in 2007 and has toured in Canada in 2008, Europe in 2008, and Australia and New Zealand in 2009. Billed as "The Most Extreme Tour of the Year", Summer Slaughter has earned a reputation as being one of the few summer tours to cater exclusively to fans of extreme forms of metal music. Starting in 2012, Summer Slaughter began to add more progressive metal bands to their lineups, seeing [[Between the Buried and Me]] co-headline with [[Cannibal Corpse]]. [[Periphery (band)|Periphery]] also played Summer Slaughter 2012, and came back during Summer Slaughter 2013, along with progressive metal bands [[Animals as Leaders]] and [[The Ocean (band)|The Ocean]]. The focus on progressive metal that year was controversial and many people were "into" heavy metal music,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kzsc.org/blog/2013/04/16/a-critical-analysis-of-the-summer-slaughter-butthurt/ |title=A Critical Analysis of the Summer Slaughter Butthurt - Music News &#124; KZSC Santa Cruz |website=Kzsc.org |date=2013-04-16 |accessdate=2016-03-08}}</ref> and death metal focused lineups returned in 2014, seeing [[Morbid Angel]] headline.
